20/02/2023, 20:30 - Cockroach: *Flipkart <Girls Wanna Code/> 4.0*

<Girls Wanna Code/> is an initiative that started out in 2018 with the objective to promote women's tech talent and give them an opportunity to work with the best minds in technology in India. The initiative aims to target women's tech talent outside premier technology campuses like IITs, NITs, etc. to ensure more equitable participation.

In previous years, students from this program, apart from securing roles at Flipkart, have bagged roles at some of the top firms.

*Eligibility*: <Girls Wanna Code/> 4.0 is open to all women engineering students pursuing a full-time B.Tech./ B.E. ( 3rd and 4th year) or M.Tech./ M.E. (All Years) degrees across branches from the selected institutes.

11/03/2023, 21:58 - Cockroach: *Applications for GSoC contributors open soon‚Ä¶*

Dates:- March 20 - April 4

Apply Link:- https://lnkd.in/dFdjQkje

GSoC explained?

GSoC stands for Google Summer of Code. It is an annual global program sponsored by Google that invites university students to participate in open-source software development projects.

The program aims to connect students with mentors from various organizations to work on coding projects during the summer break.

To participate in GSoC, students apply to work on a project proposed by an open-source organization, and if selected, they receive a stipend for the summer to work on the project.

The program helps students gain experience in open-source software development and also provides valuable contributions to the open-source community.

Google Summer of Code has been running since 2005 and has helped thousands of students and open-source organizations around the world.

23/05/2023, 17:18 - +91 86194 63019: Branching creates a new branch and you push the changes in code to the new branch..

Now when you create the PR, you should be pushing it through a new branch so that it goes through the test cases and stuff in order to check whether the code you've pushed is working perfectly or not. 

Now let's assume you're pushing the code directly to the main branch and you've created a PR. Your code has some fault and the deployment team either has to deploy your code directly to the main branch(in order to check and as it has some fault, their production will go down) or they can close the PR without merging it.
23/05/2023, 17:39 - +91 85274 12744: Think of it like a timeline concept. There is the original timeline called "master". Now you get a device that can change the timeline, you use it now the timeline is changed but it created a new parallel timeline that is called branching. You can change anything in this new branch and it won't affect the main branch until you merge the new branch with the master branch.

    // Write your code here.
    int s=0;
    for(int i=N-1,j=0;i>=0,j<N;i--,j++)
    {
        s=s+pow(2,i)*(str[j]);
    }
    return s;
}

Ye meine likha hai upar wala, jisse "wrong answer" aa raha hain output mei binary to decimal wale question mei.

Ye chatgpt ne likha hai neeche wala:

#include <bits/stdc++.h>

int convert(int N,string &str)
{
    // Write your code here.
    int s=0;
    for(int i=N-1,j=0;i>=0,j<N;i--,j++)
    {
        s=s+pow(2,i)*(str[j] - '0');
    }
    return s;
}

Is wali line mei -'0' kara hai bas aur code chal gaya to mujhe samajh nahi aa raha isse hota kya, batana isse hua kya actually?

  s=s+pow(2,i)*(str[j]¬†-¬†'0');

So You're having "7433" (say) not 7433
 Suppose You want to convert '5' to 5. So to do that Just simply do '5' - '0' , which means that 53 - 48 = 5 (ASCII Value of 0 is 48 , 1 is 49 and so on)

Hope it helped!!

With geetam, we at provokedev.tech are planning to make a community which have something for everyone who is going to participate in that community at any point of time, from any domain and for anything.

We will be hosting multiple events like., contest, seminars, interactive session and much more with the help of our geetam college outreach community which maybe available at almost every single college of India by our 1st year. On the other hand, we will be also getting working professionals at this community to help other learn the stuffs they know better.


Somewhere, we will be promoting and conserving groups, ideas, thesis/philosophy and much more of every interest/skill with the help of provokedev.tech to help them be a better version of them and their knowledge with us. Creating an ecosystem like this requires a lot of people to work collaboratively and a lot of groups, companies which will be starting with us in this project gives a preference to people who have participates in geetam at any point of time regardless of their domain as in any org/team we need people from multiple domains.

This will be foster and create a vibrant, great and amazing Open Source Community where we can do much more than our capabilities. (a) the ability to learn new technologies very quickly, 
(b) focus on high-quality work and (
c) desire to make a big impact. 

Prior experience in Golang and/or Flutter would be a huge plus. 

if you are interested in applying for the SDE Internship program (starting April 2024), 

please send a short 1-2 page biodata to Abhishek@aaritya.com
